The paper discusses data augmentation and semi-supervised learning, which are both topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of support vector machines also suggests a focus on classification problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as these sub-categories also frequently deal with classification and data augmentation techniques.
